<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-12-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-12-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="525" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Woodford</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-12-17"><hi rend="italic">December 17,
                                    1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 97.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt to-day of a telegram in cipher, which I have translated as
                            follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Woodford</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Minister, Madrid:</hi></p>
                                <p>Present our reply forthwith unless adverse reasons exist of which
                                    Department has no knowledge. In the latter case advise freely by
                                    cable.</p>
                                <p rend="right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Day</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting.</hi></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stewart L. Woodford.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>